

1️⃣ Background & Objective 

Last year we temporarily relaxed the broker Delphi cut-off to 900.
Performance within the 900–975 segment showed elevated risk, and the cut-off was subsequently tightened back to 975.

The objective of this project is to reassess the low Delphi segment, to determine whether targeted tightening rules can enable controlled expansion without increasing portfolio risk.

2️⃣ Base Population

The base population consists of 466 accounts within the 900–975 band.
Under the 3@6 definition, 50 accounts are bad, resulting in a 10.73% bad rate — much higher than our typical baseline.

We assessed both Experian and Equifax bureau variables, totalling more than 2,100 features. This broad feature space allows us to fully capture risk signals within this segment.

